The paper deals with the design of space-time codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on codes with moderate decoding complexity, which suggests a sub-category related to complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of algebraic structures in the design of codes also suggests a sub-category related to algebraic geometry or number theory (cs.AG or cs.NT). The paper also discusses the use of QR-decomposition and tree search algorithms, which are topics in numerical analysis and machine learning (cs.NI and cs.LG). Overall, cs.IT and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CC, cs.NI, and cs.LG.
